00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:26,280
my nose. There was no time to tremble. There were five minutes. Three armed men. Five hundred

495
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:31,500
guests. A man leaned against a column in the hall who had decided to stay for me and a keyboard

496
00:45:31,500 --> 00:45:37,180
beneath my hands. I started typing. The console in the mezzanine monitoring room had 14 buttons

497
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:42,360
in three screens and I knew each one of them like I knew my own handwriting. Marcello stood

498
00:45:42,360 --> 00:45:47,460
behind me. Your piece in. Repeating in a low voice the instructions the police were giving

499
00:45:47,460 --> 00:45:53,960
