538
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:26,060
Done. I said, Dario nodded once. You'll come down with me to the mezzanine hallway. He said,

539
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:32,600
then you stay. I go down to the ground floor. I'm coming with you. No. Dario. No.

540
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:38,240
The open the door. We went out into the hallway. The emergency lights had come on in a few spots.

541
00:49:38,700 --> 00:49:43,220
Giving that place the appearance of a ship that had decided to sink with class. The moss-colored

542
00:49:43,220 --> 00:49:47,840
carpet muffled the sound of footsteps. And that absence of sound made everything heavier.

543
00:49:47,840 --> 00:49:53,280
More concentrated. We went down the internal stairs. Two flights. On the landing

544
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:58,520
between the second floor and the ground floor, Dario stopped me with his palm held up in the air. Here.

545
00:49:59,020 --> 00:50:04,380
He said, here is where you stay. You listen. If the police come in before I get out,

546
00:50:04,580 --> 00:50:09,700
you open the stairwell door for them and disappear down the sweet hallway. A greed? A greed?

547
00:50:10,140 --> 00:50:17,820
You went down one more flight and disappeared around the curve. I stayed there. Pressed against the

548
00:50:17,820 --> 00:50:23,080
light that my hands trembled. Not from fear of what might happen to me. From fear of what might

549
00:50:23,080 --> 00:50:29,140
happen to him. It wasn't two minutes. It was six. I know because I counted by the hallway clock,

550
00:50:29,580 --> 00:50:34,780
which sat above a service door I'd never noticed before that night. A cheap lock with a white frame,

551
00:50:35,220 --> 00:50:39,820
completely out of keeping with the hotel's standard, which must have been left there by some employee

552
00:50:39,820 --> 00:50:44,280
on the palm. Over night shift who needed to know the time without opening his phone.

553
00:50:44,280 --> 00:50:50,800
At the fourth minute, I heard a dull thud on the floor below. A body on the ground. Two quick steps.

554
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:58,380
Silence. At the fifth, I heard a voice I recognized. Not Dario's, not Evern's. A third lower,

555
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:03,180
saying a word that sounded like an order in another language. The sound came muffled,

556
00:51:03,680 --> 00:51:08,400
as if it were coming from inside a wall. And I wondered if I was hearing it or imagining it.

557
00:51:08,740 --> 00:51:13,840
At the sixth, the service hallway door beside where I was opened. It wasn't a police officer.

558
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:21,040
It was one of the intruders. Black mask, short gun, breathless. His left shoulder darkening around a

559
00:51:21,040 --> 00:51:25,600
wound he hadn't yet noticed would bleed twice as much as it already was. He'd come up the wrong

560
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:30,880
stairs. The stairs I'd thought were locked and weren't because I'd forgotten that specific access.

561
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:35,780
The access of the fire exit that connected the ground floor directly to the mezzanine without passing

562
00:51:35,780 --> 00:51:41,680
through the elevator. He saw me before I could react. His eyes were normal. That was the frightening part.

563
00:51:41,680 --> 00:51:47,680
Ordinary eyes of someone who was afraid, bleeding, and wanting to get out of that place alive.

564
00:51:48,140 --> 00:51:54,700
He raised the gun in my direction. Where? He said, out of breath. Where's the exit? I didn't answer.

565
00:51:55,260 --> 00:52:00,460
I don't know if it was courage or if it was the surprise that froze everything. I stayed pressed

